  </music>
</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1-8): Light opening. RH 2-note close thirds, LH 3-4 note open voicing.
  G uses G-D-G-B in LH (P4+P4+m3 = large open, P4 qualifies as non-2nd).
- Phrase 2 (mm. 9-16): Dotted rhythms in melody (mm. 9-10) get matching RH motion.
  m8, m12, m16: arpeggio or spread voicing while LH sustains for textural variety.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 17-24): Repeat with RH voicing inversions varied (①² in m17, etc.).
  LH sometimes uses 1st-inversion sense voicings (e.g. D-without-root for m18 beat 2).
- Phrase 4 (mm. 25-31): Second repeat, Fuller LH (m28, m29 whole-note chords).
  m29: Em7 7th chord voicing for richer sustained sound.
- Coda (mm. 32-37): C/Em/G transition in m32 (IV-vi-I motion), ascending G arpeg in m33.
  m34: Bm-D-G-D (iv-V-I-V) strong four-chord measure. m35: Sus4 suspension.
  m37: Final convergent G whole note, full spread.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Non-diatonic substitution: C#° → D (dominant function maintained); A major → Em or D.
- mm. 7/23/36: G-D-Em-D pattern handled with stepwise inner voices throughout.
- Repeated phrases (1/3 and 2/4) use different RH voicings and inversions to avoid monotony.
- LH consistently stays in bass clef (C2-B3), P4/P5 spacing in bass.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-8: Light, 2-3 note chords, spare bass; RH arpeggios at phrase ends (m8).
- mm. 9-16: Dotted rhythms bring more motion; LH more uniform; climax at m16 whole G.
- mm. 17-24: Varied inversions enrich the repeat; sustained chords in long measures.
- mm. 25-31: Fullest LH in phrases (7th chords in m29); peak before coda.
- mm. 32-37: Coda with new C/Em color, ascending arpeg in m33 (climax);
  final resolution through sus4 (m35) → G whole (m37).
-->
